18. Diaeresis at the end of the hemistich is normal in Octonarii and usual in Septenarii. Where it is not found at the end of the fourth foot, it generally appears at the end of the fifth, eg.

Amph. 707 Noluerit salutare. Inritabis crabrones. Tace. Cape. 306 Qui imperare insuetam, nunc alterius imperio obse- quor.

(For fuller details see Klotz, Grundzic'ye, pp. 209 sqq.) Hiatus¹ is allowed at the end of the hemistich, eg.

Men. 778 nescioquid uos uelitati Ι estis inter uos duos.

For details regarding Caesura and Diaei-esis of Trochaic Verse, see Klotz, Grundzu'ye, pp. 187 sqq.‚ Podiaski, Troch. Sept. Terent. p. 19, Franks, Caesa-r. Sept. Troch. Plaut. et Terent„ Helle, 1894.
